{
  "text": "Anthropometry and body composition Anthropometric measurements were carried out in the fasted state. Body weight was measured using a digital scale accurate to 0.01 kg (Sauter, type E1200, Sauter, Ebingen, Germany) and height was measured to the nearest 0.001 m. Body mass index (BMI, kgam [CITATION_1] ) was calculated as body weight (kg) divided by height (m) squared.",
  "citation_candidates": [
